00:44.144 --> 00:47.346
I was the youngest
in a big irish catholic family.

00:47.414 --> 00:49.081
Mom was a nurse,
and dad was

00:49.149 --> 00:51.484
Custodian at the catholic
school we all attended.

00:51.552 --> 00:54.453
We didn't have much money,
but life was good,

00:54.521 --> 00:58.224
And I didn't have a care
in the world.

00:58.292 --> 01:01.727
As I got older, I started
to feel different.

01:01.795 --> 01:05.397
By the time I was a teen,
I knew I was gay.

01:05.465 --> 01:09.268
Terrified of losing my friends
and maybe even my family,

01:09.336 --> 01:10.603
I kept silent

01:10.671 --> 01:13.539
And managed to get by.

01:13.607 --> 01:15.374
As soon as I graduated
high school,

01:15.442 --> 01:17.043
I got out of town.

01:17.110 --> 01:18.778
I went off to college,

01:18.845 --> 01:21.380
Joined the Peace Corps,
and found myself

01:21.448 --> 01:23.549
Identifying with others who had
been silenced.

01:23.617 --> 01:27.987
I ended up in Washington, D.C.

01:28.055 --> 01:30.089
When Dean and I fell in love
and got married,

01:30.157 --> 01:31.624
I decided to do
what I wish

01:31.692 --> 01:33.793
I could have done
a long time ago --

01:33.860 --> 01:37.163
Be open about who I was
back in my hometown.

01:37.230 --> 01:40.032
I put our wedding announcement
in the Oil City paper,

01:40.100 --> 01:42.001
The <i>Derrick.</i>

01:42.069 --> 01:43.202
It didn't take long

01:43.270 --> 01:45.738
For the letters
to start pouring in.

01:45.806 --> 01:47.573
Woman:
"Editor: Common sense tells us

01:47.641 --> 01:49.508
Marriage is between
a man and a woman."

01:49.576 --> 01:51.744
Man: "I am shaking with anger
as I write this."

01:51.812 --> 01:53.779
Woman:
"I was sick to my stomach

01:53.847 --> 01:56.215
When I saw and read
the announcement..."

01:56.283 --> 01:59.585
Man:
"Homosexuality is immoral."

01:59.653 --> 02:01.921
Man: "It would be better
for you not to have been born.

02:01.989 --> 02:05.224
Think about that."

02:05.292 --> 02:06.892
The reactions
to my wedding announcement

02:06.960 --> 02:10.196
Were discouraging, but they
didn't really surprise me.

02:10.263 --> 02:12.932
Then I got a letter
I didn't expect.

02:13.000 --> 02:17.136
"Dear Mr. Wilson,
I searched

02:17.204 --> 02:18.904
"for your address
in Washington, D.C.,

02:18.972 --> 02:21.607
"after I saw your wedding
announcement in the paper.

02:21.675 --> 02:23.909
"I'm the mother
of a 16-year-old boy

02:23.977 --> 02:26.846
"who is being treated unjustly
because he is gay.

02:26.913 --> 02:30.182
"I was told you were
born and raised in Oil City,

02:30.250 --> 02:32.385
"so I feel
a connection to you.

02:32.452 --> 02:35.454
"Last night, my son,
C.J., cried for three hours

02:35.522 --> 02:39.125
"after being abused in public
because of being gay.

02:39.192 --> 02:41.060
"I'm so afraid for him.

02:41.128 --> 02:43.129
"I don't know where else
to turn.

02:43.196 --> 02:45.364
"Please help if you can.

02:45.432 --> 02:47.833
Sincerely,
Kathy Springer."

02:47.901 --> 02:50.503
Kathy's letter
made me realize

02:50.570 --> 02:52.938
That the controversy
about our wedding announcement

02:53.006 --> 02:54.373
Wasn't just
about gay marriage.

02:54.441 --> 02:56.042
It was about
the very existence

02:56.109 --> 02:58.010
Of openly gay people
in Oil City.

02:58.078 --> 03:02.048
Here it was, 25 years after
my own fear of being found out

03:02.115 --> 03:05.451
Forced me to live in silence,
and it didn't seem

03:05.519 --> 03:08.521
To be any easier
to be gay in my hometown.

03:08.588 --> 03:10.589
I wanted to go back
to Oil City and see

03:10.657 --> 03:13.159
If there was anything
Dean and I could do to help.

03:13.226 --> 03:14.660
Documenting people's stories

03:14.728 --> 03:16.629
Seemed like a good place
to start.

03:16.697 --> 03:18.397
So I asked Dean
to grab the camera.

