03:53.767 --> 03:56.936
Young man:
This was my school.

03:57.003 --> 03:59.472
Every day when the bus stopped

03:59.539 --> 04:03.209
And I walked through that door
to my locker

04:03.276 --> 04:05.878
Became eight hours
of pure hell.

04:11.885 --> 04:13.986
Wilson:
What went on in there?

04:14.054 --> 04:16.822
Well, kids would come by,
hit me with my locker,

04:16.890 --> 04:18.190
I'd fall on the ground,

04:18.257 --> 04:20.326
My books
would fly everywhere.

04:20.392 --> 04:22.628
I was slammed
into the lockers,

04:22.696 --> 04:25.397
Hit with stuff,
being yelled, "faggot."

04:25.465 --> 04:28.868
Yep.

04:31.671 --> 04:33.506
This hall
was always lovely.

04:33.573 --> 04:35.641
I'd have to walk
through a crowd

04:35.709 --> 04:38.844
of kids, and there would
always definitely be

04:38.912 --> 04:42.081
some tripping going on
or shoving or pushing.

04:42.149 --> 04:45.151
Grab my backpack
and yanking me,

04:45.218 --> 04:46.819
And stupid stuff.

04:46.887 --> 04:48.020
What did you feel inside

04:48.088 --> 04:49.989
When that kind of stuff
was happening?

04:50.056 --> 04:51.824
Terrified.
Nobody cared.

04:51.892 --> 04:53.159
None of the teachers
cared.

04:53.226 --> 04:54.693
None of
the administrators cared.

04:54.761 --> 04:56.495
They always gave
a deaf ear

04:56.563 --> 04:57.863
And a blind eye.

04:57.931 --> 05:01.333
They'd watch everything,
never say a word.

05:05.138 --> 05:06.505
Wilson:
I wanted to understand

05:06.573 --> 05:09.742
What was behind the anti-gay
sentiment in the area.

05:09.810 --> 05:12.011
It seemed like
talking with people

05:12.078 --> 05:14.046
Who denounced our wedding
announcement in the paper

05:14.114 --> 05:15.514
Would be a logical place
to start.

05:15.582 --> 05:19.351
Only one couple
agreed to be interviewed --

05:19.419 --> 05:21.453
Pastor Mark Micklos
and his wife, Diana.

05:21.521 --> 05:25.157
If I grant two men
the right to get married,

05:25.225 --> 05:27.960
What's wrong with incest?

05:28.028 --> 05:30.362
Or polygamy or --
and it would just,

05:30.430 --> 05:32.965
Just expand,
and I think that things --

05:33.033 --> 05:35.434
I think at times
we've seen that happen.

05:35.502 --> 05:37.403
In plumbing,
there's fittings,

05:37.470 --> 05:40.072
and they're called
male and female fittings.

05:40.140 --> 05:42.842
And you could probably

05:42.909 --> 05:45.778
plumb a house
with all male fittings,

05:45.846 --> 05:50.749
but it seems like the design
is for male and female.

05:50.817 --> 05:53.285
Not for two likes
to be together.

05:53.353 --> 05:56.655
It was hard to listen to what
the Micklosses were saying,

05:56.723 --> 05:59.058
But the fact that they
invited us to their home

05:59.125 --> 06:01.293
and we were talking
seemed like an opening.

06:01.361 --> 06:03.295
When I asked them why
they had taken the trouble

06:03.363 --> 06:05.030
to write about
our wedding announcement,

06:05.098 --> 06:07.633
they told me that their church
had received an alert

06:07.701 --> 06:09.668
that asked members
to write in protest.

06:09.736 --> 06:11.971
It was sent
by the Pennsylvania arm

06:12.038 --> 06:14.840
Of the American Family
Association,

06:14.908 --> 06:16.775
A conservative values
organization

06:16.843 --> 06:17.943
based in Mississippi.

06:18.011 --> 06:19.278
How did they key in

06:19.346 --> 06:21.881
on our little wedding
announcement so fast?

06:21.948 --> 06:24.450
It turns out that the AFA's
chapter president,

06:24.517 --> 06:26.952
Diane Gramley,
lives right there in the area

06:27.020 --> 06:29.388
and has a program
on a local radio station.

06:29.456 --> 06:33.025
<i>[ music plays ]</i>

06:33.093 --> 06:34.326
<i>Woman: Welcome to</i>

06:34.394 --> 06:36.729
<i>"American Family Focus</i>
<i>on Pennsylvania issues,"</i>

06:36.796 --> 06:38.664
<i>A weekly program</i>
<i>which discusses</i>

06:38.732 --> 06:41.100
<i>some of the happenings</i>
<i>that are of concern</i>

06:41.167 --> 06:43.035
<i>to the family</i>
<i>and those who hold</i>

06:43.103 --> 06:44.603
<i>traditional values</i>
<i>in Pennsylvania.</i>

06:44.671 --> 06:46.205
<i>And now your host,</i>

06:46.273 --> 06:49.074
<i>Diane Gramley, State Director</i>
<i>of American Family Association</i>

06:49.142 --> 06:50.576
<i>of Pennsylvania.</i>

06:50.644 --> 06:52.244
<i>Gramley: The question</i>
<i>comes down to:</i>

06:52.312 --> 06:54.179
<i>should a lifestyle that will</i>
<i>result in the destruction</i>

06:54.247 --> 06:55.915
<i>Of traditional marriage</i>
<i>and the natural family --</i>

06:55.982 --> 06:57.316
<i>not even mentioning</i>

06:57.384 --> 06:59.585
<i>the physical, mental,</i>
<i>and psychological dangers</i>

06:59.653 --> 07:01.487
<i>to those involved</i>
<i>in this lifestyle --</i>

07:01.554 --> 07:03.989
<i>be normalized and codified</i>
<i>into the laws of the land?</i>

07:04.057 --> 07:07.126
<i>Those involved in this</i>
<i>lifestyle are sinners,</i>

07:07.193 --> 07:09.395
<i>and they need to accept</i>
<i>the saving grace</i>

07:09.462 --> 07:11.563
<i>of Jesus Christ,</i>
<i>just like you and me.</i>

07:11.631 --> 07:13.699
Wilson: Back when
I was growing up,

07:13.767 --> 07:16.335
People didn't talk about
lifestyle so openly.

07:16.403 --> 07:17.903
And at my house,

07:17.971 --> 07:21.140
sexuality or being gay
wasn't discussed at all.

07:21.207 --> 07:22.841
Even though right on our street,

07:22.909 --> 07:24.843
just two doors down
from our house,

07:24.911 --> 07:27.780
we had a neighbor with
a rainbow flag on her door.

07:27.847 --> 07:30.182
Woman: I've lived
in this community

07:30.250 --> 07:33.252
since I was 17 years old,
and I've always been open.

07:33.320 --> 07:35.454
I mean, I never wore
my sexuality on a sleeve,

07:35.522 --> 07:37.122
but people always
knew who I was.

07:37.190 --> 07:41.293
Nobody was ever negative to me,
except one occasion.

07:41.361 --> 07:43.595
I was hired at this firm,

07:43.663 --> 07:45.731
and I worked there
about six months,

07:45.799 --> 07:47.933
and then the president
of the company,

07:48.001 --> 07:50.869
after the Christmas party --
and I took my partner --

07:50.937 --> 07:53.105
came in a few days later
and fired me.

07:53.173 --> 07:54.773
Said he couldn't have the likes

07:54.841 --> 07:56.675
of somebody like me
working for the company.

07:56.743 --> 07:58.377
Okay.

07:58.445 --> 08:00.546
Be good, you guys.

08:00.613 --> 08:02.715
Come here.
Come on.

08:05.218 --> 08:07.219
This is my house

08:07.287 --> 08:10.089
where my stepdad
sells smelly birds.

08:10.156 --> 08:12.691
Wilson: <i>"choo-kers?"</i>
<i>chukars or something like that?</i>
<i>Chukars.</i>

08:12.759 --> 08:15.427
Chukars, quails,
