08:15.495 --> 08:17.096
Probably stinks.

08:17.163 --> 08:18.430
Yeah, it stinks.

08:18.498 --> 08:21.934
Okay, the smell is
a little too much.

08:22.002 --> 08:24.803
Okay, it's a little
too real.

08:24.871 --> 08:27.940
That is not a place for --

08:28.008 --> 08:31.076
Bills: The first day we came
back from Christmas vacation,

08:31.144 --> 08:32.544
this kid, Richie,,

08:32.611 --> 08:35.179
who everybody's known
he was gay since, like,

08:35.248 --> 08:37.616
the day he was born,
came back to school.

08:37.683 --> 08:40.519
And I went into
my history class,

08:40.587 --> 08:42.453
last period of the day,

08:42.522 --> 08:44.957
and some kid stood up
and came over to him --

08:45.025 --> 08:46.959
'cause he was
standing by the door

08:47.027 --> 08:49.528
'cause he didn't have
a seat or anything yet --

08:49.596 --> 08:52.131
and some kid was like,
"hey, are you a faggot?"

08:52.198 --> 08:53.799
And I stood up,
and I got in his face,

08:53.867 --> 08:55.567
and I was like,
"why you got to call him that?

08:55.635 --> 08:56.902
"What did he do to you?

08:56.970 --> 08:58.804
"he's just standing there,
hasn't said a word to anybody.

08:58.872 --> 09:00.105
Leave him alone."

09:00.173 --> 09:03.042
And he's like, "What? So are
you a hard-ass homo then?"

09:03.109 --> 09:05.244
He's like, "You think
you can take me?"

09:05.311 --> 09:06.945
And I was like, "Dude,
I might be a faggot,

09:07.013 --> 09:08.480
but I'm more of a man
than you'll be."

09:08.548 --> 09:10.082
And he's like,
"So you're admitting it?"

09:10.150 --> 09:11.417
And I was like,
"I am admitting

09:11.484 --> 09:13.419
"that if you say another
word to me like that again,

09:13.486 --> 09:14.853
I am going to take
your teeth out."

09:14.921 --> 09:16.889
There was a lot he
didn't even tell me,

09:16.956 --> 09:18.390
you know, at first,

09:18.458 --> 09:19.925
because he'd come home,

09:19.993 --> 09:21.693
and he'd be real quiet,
and he'd go to his room,

09:21.761 --> 09:24.096
and he wouldn't
come out for hours.

09:24.164 --> 09:25.931
I said, "You know, c.J.,

09:25.999 --> 09:29.601
"there is nothing you could
possibly be in this world

09:29.669 --> 09:32.538
that would ever make
me stop loving you."

09:32.605 --> 09:36.408
So then, finally,
one day, he says,

09:36.476 --> 09:39.144
"I'm tired of denying
who I am,

09:39.212 --> 09:41.547
"and I'm tired
of the abuse

09:41.614 --> 09:44.516
"and the harassment
that gays take,

09:44.584 --> 09:46.452
"and I'm just
coming out with it.

09:46.519 --> 09:48.120
I don't care."

