10:40.740 --> 10:43.275
Wilson: Oil City became
a real boomtown back in 1859

10:43.343 --> 10:45.677
when colonel Edwin Drake

10:45.745 --> 10:48.080
drilled the first oil well
in the United States.

10:48.148 --> 10:51.550
The area had about 100 years of
growth and prosperity,

10:51.618 --> 10:54.987
but by the time I came along,
the wells had dried up,

10:55.054 --> 10:57.689
and jobs and people
were moving out.

10:57.757 --> 10:59.825
It had become the sort
of rust belt town

10:59.893 --> 11:01.860
that time seemed
to be leaving behind,

11:01.928 --> 11:03.529
Where things didn't change much

11:03.596 --> 11:05.531
and outsiders were viewed
with suspicion.

11:05.598 --> 11:08.700
Like many small towns,

11:08.768 --> 11:10.903
Oil City is trying
to make a comeback.

11:10.970 --> 11:12.571
If it can figure out

11:12.639 --> 11:14.473
how to use
its small-town spirt

11:14.541 --> 11:16.608
to make everyone
feel welcome there,

11:16.676 --> 11:18.677
it just might happen.

11:18.745 --> 11:21.446
