26:46.138 --> 26:48.473
Wilson: It was great

26:48.540 --> 26:50.141
to see C.J.
out of the house.

26:50.209 --> 26:53.778
But I didn't want to make him
nervous around his friends.

26:53.846 --> 26:57.648
I told him I'd catch up
with him later.

26:57.716 --> 27:00.118
[ band playing ]

27:02.788 --> 27:04.422
Bills: When I was leaving
the game,

27:04.490 --> 27:06.624
there was a whole group
of skater kids outside,

27:06.692 --> 27:07.925
Like, "are you still gay?"

27:07.993 --> 27:10.428
I went, "I ain't a faggot.
What you talking about?"

27:10.496 --> 27:11.762
And they were like, "oh, okay."

27:11.830 --> 27:14.332
And they just watched me
walk away and stuff,

27:14.399 --> 27:17.435
And I was like,
oh, god -- damn.

27:17.503 --> 27:19.170
Wilson: You know, once you
kind of come out,

27:19.238 --> 27:20.872
I mean, it's hard to, like --

27:20.939 --> 27:22.140
Go back in?

27:22.207 --> 27:23.174
Yeah.

27:23.242 --> 27:24.342
Noticed.

27:24.409 --> 27:25.877
Yeah.

27:25.944 --> 27:28.880
I actually had people
talk to me

27:28.947 --> 27:30.114
on Friday.

27:30.182 --> 27:31.382
I never -- that hasn't happened

27:31.450 --> 27:32.650
since last year.

27:32.718 --> 27:34.585
Wilson: Yeah, we noticed
a lot of people

27:34.653 --> 27:36.821
came up and kind of greeted you,
gave you a hug.

27:36.889 --> 27:38.089
Mm-hmm.

27:38.157 --> 27:39.790
And that's because they think

27:39.858 --> 27:42.160
you're not what
they thought you were?

27:42.227 --> 27:43.461
Mm-mm, cover it up.

27:43.529 --> 27:46.664
At least until I get
away from here.

27:46.732 --> 27:51.202
Springer: You shouldn't have to
live in denial, you know?

27:51.270 --> 27:52.737
But I know
there's been times

27:52.804 --> 27:54.505
Where he wished
he would have just

27:54.573 --> 27:56.874
kept his mouth shut,
and nobody would know, and --

27:56.942 --> 27:58.809
Bills: Oh, every time
I go into public,

27:58.877 --> 28:01.179
I wish I wouldn't ever
opened my mouth.

28:01.246 --> 28:04.715
Every single day.

28:04.783 --> 28:05.983
It's hell.

28:06.051 --> 28:08.186
It's not like D.C.
Or New York,

28:08.253 --> 28:09.921
where everybody's liberal.

28:09.988 --> 28:12.356
I get threatened
to get killed.

28:12.424 --> 28:14.525
That ain't fun.

28:19.431 --> 28:21.766
Hi.

28:21.833 --> 28:24.068
Wilson: I'm here tonight
to say that I'm deeply concerned

28:24.136 --> 28:26.404
at the charges of harassment,
violence, and discrimination

28:26.471 --> 28:28.839
that have ruled the Franklin
school district

28:28.907 --> 28:30.374
for the past year and a half.

28:30.442 --> 28:32.610
Gay students and students
of color at the high school

28:32.678 --> 28:34.712
have been the primary targets
of these activities.

28:34.780 --> 28:37.014
Their ability
to speak for themselves

28:37.082 --> 28:38.683
is greatly hampered by fears

28:38.750 --> 28:41.185
of backlash
if they do so publicly.

28:41.253 --> 28:42.353
Death threats have been issued

28:42.421 --> 28:43.955
against students
in this school district

28:44.022 --> 28:46.123
and it just pains me

28:46.191 --> 28:47.825
that no action
has actually been taken.

28:47.893 --> 28:49.727
So thank you for accepting
these comments

28:49.795 --> 28:51.262
in the public record --
I appreciate it,

28:51.330 --> 28:52.663
and I look forward
to your response.

28:52.731 --> 28:54.765
Woman: Thank you.

28:54.833 --> 28:57.301
Any other visitors
at this time?

28:57.369 --> 28:59.837
Wilson: It was obvious
that the school board

28:59.905 --> 29:02.540
wasn't concerned about C.J.
or <i>any</i> gay student.

29:02.608 --> 29:05.876
But the problem wasn't
just with the school.

29:05.944 --> 29:08.846
<i>Man: It can happen</i>
<i>to your town.</i>

29:08.914 --> 29:10.281
<i>AFA presents a look</i>
<i>at how</i>

29:10.349 --> 29:12.717
<i>a handful of homosexual</i>
<i>activists changed the very</i>

29:12.784 --> 29:14.118
<i>moral fiber of the city.</i>

29:14.186 --> 29:15.186
<i>They are taking over...</i>

29:15.254 --> 29:16.420
Wilson: This video
is being promoted

29:16.488 --> 29:17.622
by a local Christian
radio station

29:17.689 --> 29:19.357
to counter increasingly visible

29:19.424 --> 29:20.691
gay people in Oil City.

29:20.759 --> 29:21.859
<i>As Christian people.</i>

29:21.927 --> 29:23.527
<i>Announcer: Learn</i>
<i>the strategies used</i>

29:23.595 --> 29:25.129
<i>by gay activists</i>
<i>and don't let this</i>

29:25.197 --> 29:26.163
<i>happen to your city.</i>

29:26.231 --> 29:27.498
<i>Man:</i>
<i>If it's not happened</i>

29:27.566 --> 29:28.566
<i>in your town, get ready,</i>

29:28.634 --> 29:29.834
<i>'cause it is</i>
<i>going to happen.</i>

29:29.901 --> 29:31.502
<i>Announcer: Purchase your copy</i>

29:31.570 --> 29:33.971
<i>or a five-pack</i>
<i>to share with others today,</i>

29:34.039 --> 29:35.206
<i>and spread the news.</i>

29:35.274 --> 29:38.175
<i>They're coming to your town.</i>

29:38.243 --> 29:40.711
[ chainsaw buzzing ]

29:44.716 --> 29:46.417
Is that too long?

29:46.485 --> 29:47.852
Henderson: No,
that's probably okay.

29:47.919 --> 29:49.787
That's my chainsaw,
by the way.

29:49.855 --> 29:50.821
Mine disappeared.

29:50.889 --> 29:52.823
I don't know
where mine went.

29:52.891 --> 29:54.792
Wilson: You each have
your own chainsaw?

29:54.860 --> 29:56.027
I used to.

29:56.094 --> 29:57.228
[ chuckling ]
Whose is bigger?

29:57.296 --> 29:59.263
Hers would be
bigger.

29:59.331 --> 30:02.099
I bet I've cut more wood
than she has, though.

30:02.167 --> 30:05.336
Narrator: Roxanne can complain
about a small gene pool,

30:05.404 --> 30:07.505
But she found
a really great mate.

30:07.572 --> 30:09.940
When Linda caught wind
of the AFA video

30:10.008 --> 30:11.509
about gays coming to town,

30:11.576 --> 30:13.544
she composed
a poetic response.

30:13.612 --> 30:15.079
Henderson:
Why do you suppose

30:15.147 --> 30:17.181
there are empty store fronts?S?

30:17.249 --> 30:19.317
They're choking
our town.

30:19.384 --> 30:23.054
Why do you suppose
there's a brain drain?

30:23.121 --> 30:25.289
They're choking
our town.

30:25.357 --> 30:29.427
Why do you suppose
there is no unique art?

30:29.494 --> 30:32.630
They're choking
our town.

30:32.698 --> 30:34.298
It's time for a change.

30:34.366 --> 30:38.836
Stop choking our town.

30:40.972 --> 30:42.039
You like that?

30:42.107 --> 30:43.541
Mm-hmm.

30:43.608 --> 30:45.443
Woman: Hi, guys!

30:45.510 --> 30:47.111
Come on in!

30:47.179 --> 30:48.913
Wilson: Another case
of anti-gay discrimination

30:48.980 --> 30:51.782
had taken place several years
earlier in Titusville,

30:51.850 --> 30:54.652
a town just up the road
from Oil City.

30:54.720 --> 30:57.121
It involved a student
named Tim Dahle.

30:57.189 --> 30:58.989
I thought he and his family
might be able

30:59.057 --> 31:00.624
to help Kathy and C.J.
figure out

31:00.692 --> 31:03.260
how to get their school district
to take them more seriously.

31:03.328 --> 31:04.495
Bills: The whole thing
started

31:04.563 --> 31:06.197
from me standing up
for one kid.

31:06.264 --> 31:07.365
And no one ever,

31:07.432 --> 31:09.467
ever once said
a word to anybody.

31:09.534 --> 31:11.102
They just stood there,
my best friends,

31:11.169 --> 31:12.269
people that I've known

31:12.337 --> 31:14.004
since I was this big.

31:14.072 --> 31:15.773
They just rolled
their eyes.

31:15.841 --> 31:16.907
Man: You call them
your friends,

31:16.975 --> 31:17.942
you trust them,
and then

31:18.009 --> 31:19.210
all of a sudden,
they turn on you.

31:19.277 --> 31:21.145
I've been there.

31:21.213 --> 31:23.681
What really irritates me
is the fact

31:23.749 --> 31:26.050
that I used to
go out of my way

31:26.118 --> 31:30.621
to actually cause bodily harm
to gay people.

31:30.689 --> 31:34.392
Okay, we used to use it
like a sport, you know?

31:34.459 --> 31:36.227
I mean, it was stupid.

31:36.294 --> 31:37.862
And then when you
came out of the closet

31:37.929 --> 31:39.997
and told me that you were gay,
I thought,

31:40.065 --> 31:41.699
"oh, no, no, no.
You can't be."

31:41.767 --> 31:43.200
And I got to thinking,

31:43.268 --> 31:45.236
that gay kid's yours.

31:45.303 --> 31:47.004
You going to disown him

31:47.072 --> 31:49.740
because of his
sexual orientation?

31:49.808 --> 31:52.476
Or are you going to love him
for who he is inside?

31:52.544 --> 31:53.978
And I thought,
"the hell with it.

31:54.045 --> 31:55.846
I'm going to love him
for who he is inside."

31:55.914 --> 31:59.517
All right, and I tell you what,
you try to shed 40 years

31:59.584 --> 32:02.086
Of hatred overnight.

32:02.154 --> 32:03.387
It's just not done.

32:03.455 --> 32:06.524
It's something you
got to learn how to live with,

32:06.591 --> 32:09.026
deal with, and you
got to be sincere.

32:09.094 --> 32:10.194
I mean, he's my kid.

32:10.262 --> 32:12.363
I'm not going to turn my back
on him.

32:12.431 --> 32:15.966
I won't -- I won't never
turn my back on him.

32:16.034 --> 32:18.502
I -- I gotta eat.
See you guys.

32:18.570 --> 32:20.371
Wilson: All right.
Thanks, Ron.

32:20.439 --> 32:23.073
Woman: I can't believe
you got him on camera.

32:23.141 --> 32:24.308
Shock of all shocks!

32:24.376 --> 32:28.045
I never thought
that would happen.

32:28.113 --> 32:29.346
Wilson:
It seemed like Kathy

32:29.414 --> 32:30.815
really perked up
when Diane told her

32:30.882 --> 32:33.150
that their lawsuit had forced
the school district

32:33.218 --> 32:34.618
to implement diversity training

32:34.686 --> 32:36.320
that included
sexual orientation.

32:36.388 --> 32:37.755
Diane: We were
the first people

32:37.823 --> 32:38.989
in all these years

32:39.057 --> 32:41.258
to stand up
to our school system.

32:41.326 --> 32:43.861
And it was because what they
were doing was wrong.

32:43.929 --> 32:44.995
Yeah.

32:45.063 --> 32:46.430
Springer: It breaks my heart.

32:46.498 --> 32:48.966
I mean, I could just cry.

32:49.034 --> 32:51.469
And that there are
other kids out there

32:51.536 --> 32:53.737
going through
similar situations --

32:53.805 --> 32:55.639
None of this
should ever happen.

32:55.707 --> 32:58.442
I don't know that I'll
change the world,

32:58.510 --> 33:01.846
but if I can even just
educate a few people, like,

33:01.913 --> 33:05.916
look, they weren't put on this
earth to be tortured like this.

33:10.755 --> 33:12.823
We're getting ready
for the grand opening.

33:12.891 --> 33:14.291
And all of a sudden,

33:14.359 --> 33:17.928
Diane Gramley sent out
a letter

33:17.996 --> 33:22.266
warning everyone about
how dangerous we are and --

33:22.334 --> 33:24.401
we have this
homosexual agenda.

33:24.469 --> 33:26.971
And her brother
goes to work with a guy

33:27.038 --> 33:29.573
whose minister stood
right in the pulpit

33:29.641 --> 33:31.775
and said to boycott
the Latonia.

33:31.843 --> 33:33.777
What?

33:33.845 --> 33:35.045
Where is that
coming from?

33:35.113 --> 33:36.146
Diane Gramley.

33:36.214 --> 33:37.414
She's started
an all-in, all-out

33:37.482 --> 33:39.483
campaign against us.

33:39.551 --> 33:40.985
And she's saying
to people,

33:41.052 --> 33:42.553
"don't do business
with the Latonia"?

33:42.621 --> 33:43.621
Yes.

33:43.688 --> 33:45.222
Because it's run
by a lesbian couple.

33:45.290 --> 33:48.158
Yes -- we just wanted
to have a business.

33:48.226 --> 33:51.061
If all the city wants
is churches,

33:51.129 --> 33:52.530
then what do they need

33:52.597 --> 33:54.331
an Art Deco theater for?

33:58.403 --> 34:00.237
Wilson: As we were dealing
with anti-gay attitudes

34:00.305 --> 34:01.438
right there
in the community,

34:01.506 --> 34:02.973
the state of Pennsylvania

34:03.041 --> 34:06.176
was considering expanding
its anti-discrimination law

34:06.244 --> 34:08.512
to include
sexual orientation.

34:08.580 --> 34:10.214
Kathy was invited
to tell her story

34:10.282 --> 34:12.783
about discrimination at C.J.'s
school at a public hearing.

34:12.851 --> 34:14.784
I'm not a public speaker.

34:14.853 --> 34:17.888
But -- and I don't know
what I'd say.

34:17.956 --> 34:22.326
I just, I need to hear
how it's going and --

34:22.393 --> 34:23.960
Wilson: I've printed out
a copy of the law,

34:24.029 --> 34:25.496
so we can look at it.
Okay, good, good.

34:25.563 --> 34:27.031
Yeah, that would be good.

34:27.098 --> 34:28.799
Where you see
the underline,

34:28.867 --> 34:31.068
it's trying to add
"sexual orientation,

34:31.136 --> 34:33.603
Gender identity,
or expression."

34:33.672 --> 34:35.371
You know,
I don't understand

34:35.440 --> 34:39.643
where they even get off
not including

34:39.710 --> 34:41.612
gay and lesbian.

34:41.679 --> 34:43.246
You know, let's get,
you know,

34:43.315 --> 34:45.416
our heads
out of our asses here.

34:49.154 --> 34:51.021
<i>Gramley: On June 13th,</i>
<i>A homosexual special rights</i>

34:51.089 --> 34:52.556
<i>Bill was introduced</i>
<i>in Harrisburg.</i>

34:52.623 --> 34:55.391
<i>This is Diane Gramley with</i>
<i>the American Family Assocition</i>

34:55.460 --> 34:57.227
<i>of Pennsylvania,</i>
<i>with a call to action.</i>

34:57.295 --> 34:59.396
<i>Advocates for the passage</i>
<i>of these bills</i>

34:59.464 --> 35:01.231
<i>deny they are</i>
<i>special rights bills,</i>

35:01.299 --> 35:03.801
<i>But in what other situation</i>
<i>is a law specifically written</i>

35:03.868 --> 35:05.502
<i>to include a group of people</i>

35:05.570 --> 35:08.172
<i>simply because of the sexual</i>
<i>activity in which they engage?</i>

35:08.239 --> 35:10.908
<i>They have never been required</i>
<i>to sit in the back of the bus</i>

35:10.976 --> 35:13.277
<i>or drink from designated</i>
<i>water fountains.</i>

35:13.345 --> 35:15.746
<i>They've never been considered</i>
<i>less than human,</i>

35:15.814 --> 35:17.381
<i>as African Americans</i>
<i>once were.</i>

35:17.449 --> 35:18.782
<i>Homosexual activists</i>
<i>are trying</i>

35:18.850 --> 35:20.451
<i>to hijack</i>
<i>the civil rights movement</i>

35:20.518 --> 35:21.652
<i>by pulling the victim card</i>

35:21.720 --> 35:23.354
<i>and trying to seek</i>
<i>the normalization</i>

35:23.421 --> 35:24.888
<i>of their destructive</i>
<i>lifestyle.</i>

35:24.956 --> 35:27.157
Wilson:
People like Diane

35:27.225 --> 35:29.493
are using misinformation

35:29.561 --> 35:31.996
to stir up irrational fears,
to kind of

35:32.063 --> 35:34.198
push people
back into the closet.

35:34.265 --> 35:35.733
It's not going to happen.

35:35.800 --> 35:37.067
But when they
stir up that fear,

35:37.135 --> 35:38.235
that's what creates
the problems.

35:38.303 --> 35:39.703
That's what puts
people like C.J. at risk.

35:39.771 --> 35:40.738
At risk.
Okay.

35:40.805 --> 35:41.839
Because those messages

35:41.906 --> 35:43.407
go out there and say,
"Oh, those are

35:43.475 --> 35:44.908
the people
we're supposed to hate."

35:44.976 --> 35:46.343
You know, can you imagine,
I mean,

35:46.411 --> 35:49.213
just seeing somebody
at a party and saying,

35:49.280 --> 35:50.748
"Oh, that's the faggot.

35:50.815 --> 35:53.517
"Let's go, you know,
punch him, literally

35:53.585 --> 35:54.585
knock him out --"

35:54.653 --> 35:56.220
Can I imagine that?
Oh, yeah.

35:56.287 --> 35:58.288
I-I <i>can</i> imagine that.

35:58.356 --> 36:03.093
I mean, I was that type
of a person at one time.

36:03.161 --> 36:06.530
Now, that may be shocking
to you.

36:06.598 --> 36:10.067
But in my journey in life,
I'm no longer like that,

36:10.135 --> 36:11.669
And a big part of that

36:11.736 --> 36:14.304
Is my Christianity,
my faith in Christ.

36:14.372 --> 36:17.307
You know, I truly believe
that Jesus Christ

36:17.375 --> 36:21.478
has changed my character,
so that I don't do that,

36:21.546 --> 36:23.080
nor do I want
to do those things anymore.

36:23.148 --> 36:24.882
I mean, those are wrong.
It's wrong to do that.

36:24.949 --> 36:26.216
It's wrong to violate...

36:26.284 --> 36:28.519
You know, anybody.

36:28.586 --> 36:30.688
I became
a different person.

36:30.755 --> 36:33.023
Do you think there will come
a time, though, when we

36:33.091 --> 36:35.926
don't disagree about

36:35.994 --> 36:37.494
the place that gay, lesbian,

36:37.562 --> 36:40.030
bisexual, and trans people
have in the world?

36:40.098 --> 36:43.867
Maybe aspects of it.
I don't know.

36:43.935 --> 36:45.169
I don't know.

36:45.236 --> 36:46.837
You know...

36:46.905 --> 36:50.074
I'd have to...

36:50.141 --> 36:52.176
That would be a big --
that would be

36:52.243 --> 36:54.011
a big change for me,
you know?

36:54.079 --> 36:56.947
Wilson: My interactions
with Pastor Micklos

36:57.015 --> 36:58.849
Were odd.

36:58.917 --> 37:00.350
Ever since
the wedding announcement,

37:00.418 --> 37:02.219
I felt like I had been battling

37:02.287 --> 37:03.987
against people who use religion

37:04.055 --> 37:06.757
to deny gay people basic rights
of visibility.

37:06.825 --> 37:10.360
Pastor Micklos was open
to looking at things

37:10.428 --> 37:11.995
in a different way.

37:12.063 --> 37:13.731
I'd never thought
I'd become friends

37:13.798 --> 37:15.833
with someone who didn't
view me as his equal.

37:15.900 --> 37:19.536
But his willingness to examine
his own beliefs

37:19.604 --> 37:21.939
was helping me to see
that not all religious people

37:22.006 --> 37:24.007
fell into the box
that I often put them in.

37:24.075 --> 37:25.809
Good afternoon, joe,
how are you doing?

37:25.877 --> 37:27.311
Wilson: Hi, Diane,
how are you?

37:27.378 --> 37:29.713
I wanted to introduce you
to Kathy Springer and C.J.

37:29.781 --> 37:31.381
Oh, okay, good,
nice to meet you.

37:31.449 --> 37:33.083
Thank you, it's nice
to meet you.

37:33.151 --> 37:36.720
Wilson: C.J. Is the young boy
who was in Franklin high school

37:36.788 --> 37:39.823
and was experiencing harassment
and discrimination.

37:39.891 --> 37:41.358
Okay, the one that was
on your video?

37:41.426 --> 37:42.960
Wilson: Yeah.
What do you think of that?

37:43.027 --> 37:44.928
Well, I need to get in here
to the meeting, excuse me.

37:49.000 --> 37:49.967
Woman: Diane Gramley

37:50.034 --> 37:52.669
From the American Family
Association

37:52.737 --> 37:54.772
of Pennsylvania.

37:54.839 --> 37:55.906
Gramley: Civil rights
protections

37:55.974 --> 37:56.907
have long
been fought for

37:56.975 --> 37:58.942
by disenfranchised groups
of people.

37:59.010 --> 38:03.080
African Americans led the fight
for civil rights,

38:03.148 --> 38:05.048
seeking the right to vote
and to no longer

38:05.116 --> 38:07.284
be required to sit
at the back of the bus.

38:07.352 --> 38:09.386
But a person's skin color
or national origin

38:09.454 --> 38:10.687
is unchangeable.

38:10.755 --> 38:14.291
Wilson: Again, Gramley was
trying to use race

38:14.359 --> 38:16.360
as a wedge to divide.

38:16.427 --> 38:18.395
But this time, she was dealing
with legislators

38:18.463 --> 38:20.230
who were experienced
in civil rights law.

38:20.298 --> 38:23.300
I was hoping they'd be more open
to Kathy's testimony.

38:23.368 --> 38:24.835
Springer: I'm sorry,
I'm already nervous.

38:24.903 --> 38:27.171
[ laughing ]
I'm not a public speaker.

38:27.238 --> 38:29.573
At this time I'd like
to tell you

38:29.641 --> 38:31.275
about my son,
C.J. Bills.

38:31.342 --> 38:33.343
At the time,
he was 15 years old

38:33.411 --> 38:35.946
and attended a public school
in Venango county.

38:36.014 --> 38:39.349
There was an incident
on a school bus one day.

38:39.417 --> 38:41.185
He was on a field trip.

38:41.252 --> 38:42.786
There were teachers
monitoring

38:42.854 --> 38:44.588
this whole trip.

38:44.656 --> 38:46.023
Kids were throwing things

38:46.090 --> 38:48.058
at him,
calling him "faggot,"

38:48.126 --> 38:50.727
"queer," "gay,"
asking if he wanted

38:50.795 --> 38:52.996
to perform sex acts
on them.

38:53.064 --> 38:55.399
The teachers
just turned their heads

38:55.466 --> 38:57.234
and acted
like it never happened.

38:57.302 --> 38:59.269
We've had our house

38:59.337 --> 39:01.572
threatened to be
burned down.

39:01.639 --> 39:04.408
We've gotten phone calls
by these boys, saying,

39:04.475 --> 39:06.610
"we want to see
what color a faggot bleeds."

39:06.678 --> 39:10.214
He was vulnerable,
he was scared,

39:10.281 --> 39:11.815
he didn't want
to go to school.

39:11.883 --> 39:14.618
His grades were dropping.

39:14.686 --> 39:16.620
He was suicidal.

39:18.389 --> 39:22.059
I, um, I just have
one more thing

39:22.126 --> 39:25.662
to say -- I hope it never
comes to your family,

39:25.730 --> 39:27.998
where one of your children
are tortured

39:28.066 --> 39:29.366
for being who they are.

39:29.434 --> 39:32.636
Thank you.

39:32.704 --> 39:34.605
[ man coughs ]

39:34.672 --> 39:37.608
Sometimes black people
have a problem

39:37.675 --> 39:39.910
with people who are different

39:39.978 --> 39:44.047
comparing their experiences

39:44.115 --> 39:46.550
with the black experience.

39:46.618 --> 39:48.652
Because of
your experience,

39:48.720 --> 39:50.954
you're going to be able
to help other young people

39:51.022 --> 39:54.725
so that maybe tomorrow
this doesn't happen.

39:54.792 --> 39:55.859
God bless you for it.

39:55.927 --> 39:58.695
Be who you are,
no matter what.

39:58.763 --> 39:59.796
Thank you very much.

39:59.864 --> 40:03.367
Springer:
Thank you.

40:07.171 --> 40:08.839
Wilson: Diane and group,
we actually wanted

40:08.907 --> 40:10.307
to ask you how you respond

40:10.375 --> 40:13.010
to the very personal testimonies
of C.J. And Kathy.

40:13.077 --> 40:15.178
Like I said at the beginning
of my testimony,

40:15.246 --> 40:16.847
I thought it was
awful information.

40:16.915 --> 40:19.283
And the Franklin school district
should not have done to him

40:19.350 --> 40:20.350
what they permitted to do.

40:20.418 --> 40:21.418
So will you join us

40:21.486 --> 40:22.953
in fighting discrimination --
No --

40:23.021 --> 40:24.821
Against gay and lesbian
people in Franklin?

40:24.889 --> 40:25.956
Not, we're not going to --

40:26.024 --> 40:27.257
We're not
going to join you.

40:27.325 --> 40:28.425
Why not?
No.

40:28.493 --> 40:32.930
Because of the roads
that that will open.

40:32.997 --> 40:36.333
Wilson: Kathy's testimony
may not have influenced Gramley,

40:36.401 --> 40:38.669
but it did have an impact
on the legislators.

40:38.736 --> 40:40.704
After the hearing,

40:40.772 --> 40:43.874
one of the staff offered to help
Kathy and C.J. Contact the ACLU

40:43.942 --> 40:46.543
to press a legal case
against their school district.

40:46.611 --> 40:49.313
Springer: Prior to this,
I figured, the ACLU --

40:49.380 --> 40:50.414
What the heck?

40:50.481 --> 40:52.049
All they can do
is tell me no, you know.

40:52.116 --> 40:54.584
Well, the next thing
I know,

40:54.652 --> 40:56.720
I got a return phone call.

40:56.788 --> 40:58.755
And we had
a great lawyer

40:58.823 --> 41:02.759
From the ACLU.

41:06.965 --> 41:08.899
Wilson: What do you think
about the Latonia?

41:08.967 --> 41:11.001
Boy: I'm glad
that Roxanne got it,

41:11.069 --> 41:12.803
because there was a guy
that wanted to scrap

41:12.870 --> 41:14.271
the whole place out
piece by piece.

41:14.339 --> 41:17.774
And look at that --
that picture

41:17.842 --> 41:19.743
of that chandelier.

41:19.811 --> 41:22.913
It's just, like, scary!

41:22.981 --> 41:24.915
It could fall any second!

41:24.983 --> 41:27.484
And plus, it's great!

41:32.957 --> 41:35.692
Wilson: Just two days
before the grand opening,

41:35.760 --> 41:37.861
Roxanne and linda got a call
from a neighboring

41:37.929 --> 41:40.397
businessman about
their "homosexual agenda"

41:40.465 --> 41:41.598
at the Latonia.

41:41.666 --> 41:42.933
What happened on that
phone call you got?

41:43.001 --> 41:44.201
Hitchcock: I said,

41:44.268 --> 41:46.169
"if you want to listen to people
like Diane Gramley,"

41:46.237 --> 41:47.504
I said, "you're welcome to,
but," I said,

41:47.572 --> 41:48.605
"you know what?

41:48.673 --> 41:49.706
"we're trying
to do something

41:49.774 --> 41:51.375
Wonderful
for the community here."

41:51.442 --> 41:53.477
And I said, "I want to know
what Diane Gramley

41:53.544 --> 41:55.145
Has done to promote
the community."

41:55.213 --> 41:56.213
Yeah.

41:56.280 --> 41:57.414
"besides her witch hunts."

41:57.482 --> 41:58.915
Yeah!
I said, "she's always

41:58.983 --> 42:00.917
on a witch hunt
about something."

42:00.985 --> 42:02.019
Did you say that?

42:02.086 --> 42:04.021
Yes, I did.

42:04.088 --> 42:08.125
Henderson: The negative messages
sting so bad

42:08.192 --> 42:09.860
that it takes, probably,

42:09.927 --> 42:12.195
100 positive
to keep you on track --

42:12.263 --> 42:15.866
when it's that hateful.

42:17.468 --> 42:19.569
Wilson: After
Kathy and C.J.'s case

42:19.637 --> 42:21.905
about discrimination
at the high school

42:21.973 --> 42:23.874
got attention
in the community,

42:23.941 --> 42:25.308
the local college
brought in

42:25.376 --> 42:27.711
a gay Christian performing arts
group from Pittsburgh

42:27.779 --> 42:30.013
to help people see things
from a youth perspective.

42:30.081 --> 42:32.349
Somehow, I managed to get

42:32.417 --> 42:34.785
C.J. And Pastor Micklos
to attend.

42:34.852 --> 42:36.186
♫ my soul ♫

42:36.254 --> 42:38.522
[ cheers and applause ]

42:38.589 --> 42:39.756
Woman: I hope
that our performance

42:39.824 --> 42:42.592
puts a face
to gay christians

42:42.660 --> 42:44.061
and puts a face

42:44.128 --> 42:45.362
to gay people.

42:45.430 --> 42:47.030
There's a lot of people
that don't know things

42:47.098 --> 42:49.332
about gay people,
and they have the stereotypical

42:49.400 --> 42:51.501
assumptions of gay people.

42:51.569 --> 42:54.071
What you just said
about stereotypes,

42:54.138 --> 42:56.540
is that reversed at times,
as well?

42:56.607 --> 42:58.909
As far as gay people having

42:58.976 --> 43:02.112
stereotypes about
straight people?

43:02.180 --> 43:03.413
Um...

43:03.481 --> 43:05.849
Man: Yeah.
I do it.

43:05.917 --> 43:07.217
I stereotype
straight people

43:07.285 --> 43:09.486
as dressing badly
and --

43:09.554 --> 43:12.222
[ laughter and applause ]

43:14.158 --> 43:17.027
Thanks for coming

43:17.095 --> 43:18.995
How did you guys meet?

43:19.063 --> 43:20.597
We wrote a letter
to the editor,

43:20.665 --> 43:22.966
and they...
captured us.

43:23.034 --> 43:25.535
And we became friends.

43:25.603 --> 43:26.870
Awesome.

43:26.938 --> 43:28.572
But I'm sorry
that part of the reason

43:28.639 --> 43:30.373
you're not in school
is because violence

43:30.441 --> 43:31.608
was perpetrated against you.

43:31.676 --> 43:35.078
Not good
under any circumstances.

43:35.146 --> 43:36.580
Bills: How did he
come around

43:36.647 --> 43:38.014
like that?

43:38.082 --> 43:39.616
Wilson: I guess
that he's been

43:39.684 --> 43:41.451
thinking about it
for a little bit.

43:41.519 --> 43:42.819
Wow.

43:42.887 --> 43:46.389
At times, we all
get stereotyped, don't we?

43:46.457 --> 43:47.958
Huh?

43:48.025 --> 43:52.328
Sometimes we're not so bad
as our first impressions are.

43:55.333 --> 43:58.001
Woman: You know
there are people

43:58.069 --> 44:00.437
who don't care
what this guy's spreading.

44:00.505 --> 44:03.406
And even if they listen,
they have seen you at work,

44:03.474 --> 44:05.909
And they have seen
everything you've done.

44:05.977 --> 44:07.777
I know, but we got
a double whammy against us.

44:07.845 --> 44:09.212
You know that.

44:09.280 --> 44:10.313
I know you do,

44:10.381 --> 44:11.982
But you have to not let this

44:12.049 --> 44:14.718
take away from what you've
worked so hard for.

44:14.785 --> 44:16.319
Please put on your face
and say,

44:16.387 --> 44:19.322
"you're not
going to do this to us."

44:19.390 --> 44:21.458
And make this just be
as wonderful

44:21.526 --> 44:22.993
an event
as it can be,

44:23.060 --> 44:24.161
and is <i>going</i> to be.

44:24.228 --> 44:25.162
What are we
going to say?

44:25.229 --> 44:26.696
Latonia!

44:26.764 --> 44:28.798
All: Latonia!

44:28.866 --> 44:30.100
See?
That's what we needed.

44:30.168 --> 44:32.302
Man: I told joe
that you and Roxanne

44:32.370 --> 44:35.405
have been working sometimes
18-hour days getting this done.

44:35.473 --> 44:37.641
I can't imagine,
because there's many <i>weeks</i>

44:37.708 --> 44:39.042
that I don't work 18 hours.

44:39.110 --> 44:40.177
[ laughing ]

44:40.244 --> 44:43.480
But it hasn't been us
by ourselves.

44:43.548 --> 44:45.282
We've had
a lot of people helping,

44:45.349 --> 44:47.751
and if you're looking now,
there's an army up there,

44:47.818 --> 44:49.419
helping us
get the room ready.

44:49.487 --> 44:52.322
For KQW 96.3
at the Latonia,

44:52.390 --> 44:53.590
I'm Sam Gordon.

44:56.360 --> 44:58.595
Gordon: Why are you
doing it?

44:58.663 --> 45:00.430
Woman:
Because I love Rox and Linda

45:00.498 --> 45:01.464
so much.

45:01.532 --> 45:04.501
That's the only reason why!

45:04.569 --> 45:06.836
[ laughing ]
Joy!

45:06.904 --> 45:08.338
I'm probably
going to cry.

45:08.406 --> 45:12.542
It's -- I --
people are coming through

45:12.610 --> 45:13.710
to let us know.

45:13.778 --> 45:15.579
♫ oh, oh, oh,
and I'm ♫

45:15.646 --> 45:16.813
♫ wrong, yeah ♫

45:16.881 --> 45:19.749
♫ but I'm still
the toughest one ♫

45:19.817 --> 45:20.951
Littler:
Listen to this.

45:21.018 --> 45:23.753
"The Latonia's very bold

45:23.821 --> 45:25.822
"and features
one of the biggest

45:25.890 --> 45:28.024
chandeliers
in the United States!"

45:28.092 --> 45:32.596
That baby is what I call
something!

45:32.663 --> 45:35.699
Wilson: Roxanne and Linda
could count on the support

45:35.766 --> 45:37.100
of their close friends.

45:37.168 --> 45:38.935
But the challenge
in small towns

45:39.003 --> 45:41.338
like Oil City is getting
regular people

45:41.405 --> 45:43.840
to show their support when it
could really make a difference.

45:43.908 --> 45:46.109
It remained to be seen
whether the community at large

45:46.177 --> 45:50.780
would show up
for the Latonia's grand opening.

45:53.384 --> 45:54.651
Okay.

45:54.719 --> 45:55.819
Wilson: Clutch all the way
to the floor,

45:55.886 --> 45:57.020
left foot.
That one?

45:57.088 --> 45:58.622
Yeah, but with
your left foot.

45:58.689 --> 46:00.824
And don't let it up.

46:00.891 --> 46:02.892
Or you'll go right through
that garage door.

46:02.960 --> 46:04.294
[ engine starts ]

46:04.362 --> 46:06.029
Now keep it down
and put it in reverse,

46:06.097 --> 46:07.197
which is
way, way, way back.

46:07.265 --> 46:08.231
That way?

46:08.299 --> 46:09.566
Over, yeah.

46:09.634 --> 46:12.902
Oh, this is a whole new
experience of the world here.

46:12.970 --> 46:15.538
♫ hey, hey ♫

46:15.606 --> 46:17.807
I'm not used to change.

46:17.875 --> 46:19.809
♫ remember when we
used to play ♫

46:19.877 --> 46:24.848
♫ out in your backyard
almost every day? ♫

46:24.915 --> 46:26.750
This is awesome!

46:26.817 --> 46:29.519
And he trusts me.

46:29.587 --> 46:31.021
That's sweet!

46:33.157 --> 46:36.526
♫ hey, hey ♫

46:36.594 --> 46:37.894
♫ remember when we used to ♫

46:37.962 --> 46:39.095
Wilson:
After two years,

46:39.163 --> 46:41.965
Kathy and C.J.,
with the help of the ACLU,

46:42.033 --> 46:44.734
finally reached a settlement
with the school district

46:44.802 --> 46:45.969
that included a promise

46:46.037 --> 46:49.873
of comprehensive
anti-discrimination training.

46:49.940 --> 46:52.008
C.J. And I drove over
to the high school

46:52.076 --> 46:53.877
To meet Kathy
and the ACLU lawyer.

46:53.944 --> 46:55.078
They were observing
the training

46:55.146 --> 46:56.212
to make sure it included

46:56.280 --> 46:58.248
sexual orientation.

46:58.316 --> 47:01.084
We had to drive my car,
because C.J.'s

47:01.152 --> 47:03.887
$150 special had already
been scrapped.

47:03.954 --> 47:06.456
And when you stop, clutch in,
if you're in gear.

47:06.524 --> 47:07.957
Clutch down, all the way
to the floor.

47:08.025 --> 47:08.958
All right.

47:09.026 --> 47:10.226
Clutch, man!

47:10.294 --> 47:12.929
Every time you stop,
you gotta use the clutch.

47:17.601 --> 47:19.769
So, how'd everything go?

47:19.837 --> 47:21.638
I wish they would have had

47:21.706 --> 47:25.041
this in-service training program
two years ago.

47:25.109 --> 47:27.210
Maybe we could have avoided

47:27.278 --> 47:28.912
all of these problems.

47:28.979 --> 47:30.413
I thought it was
very good.

47:30.481 --> 47:32.382
I was very pleased.
I was very pleased.

47:32.450 --> 47:34.684
My hands are
going to freeze off.

47:34.752 --> 47:37.387
[ laughing ]
Let's go to the restaurant.

47:38.956 --> 47:40.190
Okay, dude,
let me hear your comments.

47:40.257 --> 47:41.725
What do you think about that?
That's awesome.

47:41.792 --> 47:44.127
I want to find out
if he has, like,

47:44.195 --> 47:45.528
more programs set up,

47:45.596 --> 47:48.832
like, same thing as this,
or different ones, or...

47:48.899 --> 47:50.367
Springer:
It's taken us two years,

47:50.434 --> 47:52.102
but it's a step
that I never thought

47:52.169 --> 47:53.703
would happen.

47:53.771 --> 47:54.938
Wilson:
And quite a journey

47:55.005 --> 47:56.840
for you, I'll say.

47:56.907 --> 48:00.577
Yeah, I'm just a little old
back-hills mom.

48:00.644 --> 48:02.245
[ laughing ]
Yeah.

48:02.313 --> 48:04.013
I -- I --

48:04.081 --> 48:08.051
I'll keep
being that voice.

48:08.119 --> 48:11.388
Even if my son
moves away from this area,

48:11.455 --> 48:14.124
which he'd like
very much to do,

48:14.191 --> 48:15.892
I'm not going anywhere.

48:15.960 --> 48:17.761
I'm still going to be here,

48:17.828 --> 48:20.697
still going to stand up
against the bigots

48:20.765 --> 48:25.702
until they wake up
and...

48:25.770 --> 48:28.271
see the world
for what it is.

48:41.919 --> 48:44.921
[ jazz playing ]

48:46.991 --> 48:48.758
Welcome to the Latonia.

48:48.826 --> 48:51.528
Thank you.

49:06.677 --> 49:08.011
Woman: The spirit
of the building

49:08.078 --> 49:09.345
is alive again,
you know?

49:09.413 --> 49:10.480
It just is.

49:10.548 --> 49:12.482
I think this is just
another piece

49:12.550 --> 49:14.751
that's going to come alive
and, and add

49:14.819 --> 49:17.420
to all the other things
that are happening here.

49:17.488 --> 49:18.988
Woman:
Oh, I'm excited

49:19.056 --> 49:20.423
about the vision
and the energy

49:20.491 --> 49:21.891
that people have here
to bring this alive.

49:21.959 --> 49:23.593
It's exciting.

49:23.661 --> 49:25.462
The chandelier is gorgeous.
Yeah.

49:25.529 --> 49:28.164
I can't wait to see it
lit up.

49:31.302 --> 49:32.936
Henderson: Thank you all
for coming

49:33.003 --> 49:34.070
this evening..

49:34.138 --> 49:35.805
This is a fantastic night.

49:35.873 --> 49:38.241
[ applause ]

49:38.309 --> 49:41.511
When you start on a large
project like this,

49:41.579 --> 49:43.146
you need to celebrate

49:43.214 --> 49:45.181
some mile markers.

49:45.249 --> 49:46.282
But what's exciting

49:46.350 --> 49:48.585
to me is watching
what's happening

49:48.652 --> 49:49.919
throughout Oil City.

49:49.987 --> 49:53.590
It means a lot to me
to see all these faces,

49:53.657 --> 49:56.860
to see all these people
who are behind this project.

49:56.927 --> 49:59.963
And it hasn't always
been easy.

50:00.030 --> 50:02.565
[ voice breaking ]
and, uh, I think I'm going to

50:02.633 --> 50:04.701
Have to turn it over
to Rox right now.

50:04.768 --> 50:06.135
[ laughter ]

50:06.203 --> 50:07.937
My partner, Roxanne.

50:07.972 --> 50:10.206
[ applause ]

50:13.043 --> 50:15.245
Okay, Roxy,
are we ready?

50:15.312 --> 50:16.846
Hitchcock: Okay.

50:16.914 --> 50:18.815
All right,
One...

50:18.883 --> 50:21.017
Two...Three.

50:21.085 --> 50:24.087
[ cheers and applause ]

50:36.967 --> 50:40.236
Henderson: We actually had
imagined that moment from --

50:40.304 --> 50:41.538
For a long time.

50:41.605 --> 50:43.239
Hitchcock: Just seeing
the community's reaction to that

50:43.307 --> 50:44.941
just made it all worthwhile.

50:45.009 --> 50:48.044
That was cool!

50:48.112 --> 50:50.413
Hitchcock: We love
this old building.

50:50.481 --> 50:51.648
We're fixing it up.

50:51.715 --> 50:54.183
We want to turn it
into something viable

50:54.251 --> 50:57.186
and economically reasonable
for Oil City,

50:57.254 --> 50:58.855
but in the same token,
we're giving something

50:58.923 --> 51:00.056
back to the city.

51:00.124 --> 51:03.960
It's all about being able
to be ourselves

51:04.028 --> 51:07.363
without somebody
questioning every

51:07.431 --> 51:09.866
motive we might have.

51:09.934 --> 51:11.701
Yeah, what they call
an agenda,

51:11.769 --> 51:12.735
we call our lives.

51:12.803 --> 51:14.103
Right!
Right!

51:14.171 --> 51:17.073
♫ Everything feels like enough ♫

51:17.141 --> 51:18.474
<i>Man, on P.A.:</i>
<i>We come against</i>

51:18.542 --> 51:21.210
<i>The strongholds of sin</i>
<i>in this city</i>

51:21.278 --> 51:22.579
<i>In the name of Jesus,</i>

51:22.646 --> 51:24.814
<i>And we tear</i>
<i>those strongholds down</i>

51:24.882 --> 51:26.015
<i>In the name of Jesus.</i>

51:26.083 --> 51:27.550
<i>Father, I thank you</i>
<i>that there is</i>

51:27.618 --> 51:30.086
<i>An army of believers,</i>

51:30.154 --> 51:32.956
<i>Ready to take this city</i>
<i>for Jesus Christ.</i>

51:33.023 --> 51:36.059
♫ I want to see Jesus
lifted high ♫

51:36.126 --> 51:39.829
♫ a banner that flies
across this land ♫

51:39.897 --> 51:42.532
♫ that all men will see
the truth and know ♫

51:42.600 --> 51:45.501
♫ he is the way... ♫

